blog.title: Dream a little bigger, darling.
blog.description:
Woman.
Determined.
Braided.

What else?
Normality is overrated.
Wibbly wobbly, timey wimey.
Black, two sugars. I'll be upstairs.
One more miracle, please.

You mustn't be afraid to dream a little bigger, darling.

summary: Some Ideas for a Potential Iron Man Game in the Future
title: Some Ideas for a Potential Iron Man Game in the Future
body:
In Spider-Man PS4, each of the backpacks have items that Peter gives a brief story on.

The idea is that Tony can do the same thing for his different armor sets.

There can be different stories that he can offer for some of them such as the Modular or Hulkbuster armor.

Maybe even the Mark I armor if they ever include it in the game.

On the chance that it is set in the same universe as Spider-Man PS4, Tony can also talk about other heroes that he knows in the same manner that Peter offers his thoughts on T’Challa or the West Coast Avengers.

Another idea would be customizable loadouts for the same armor.

Or flight challenges similar to the drone challenges. Maybe Taskmaster could show up in this game.

Anyways, what are your thoughts? ^_^

summary: Tom Holland and Marvel have no idea how much influence they’ve had on my family
body:
Tom Holland and Marvel have no idea how much influence they’ve had on my family

Like you can’t say anything in this household without it turning into a Spider-man reference. Like the other day while doing dishes my aunt saw a cup of chai (tea) and so she asked ‘is this anyone’s chai?’ And simultaneously me, my cousin and her younger sister who is like 9 started laughing because it sounded like ‘ is this anyone’s bike?’ from Homecoming and we haven’t let that go since.

Another cousin of mine wants a spider man themed party for his 3rd birthday because me and my previously mentioned cousin like him and have forced him to watch the movie with us like a billion times.

My 9 year old cousin also has all the lines memorized from most of the marvel movies because of us.

My cousin also has Tom Holland as her lock screen and talks about him so much that my aunt refers to him as her son-in-law now.

I could go on for like 2 hours talking about marvel and especially Tom holland related instances that have occurred and like wow we all need help man 😂😂
